_":28,"ana":29,"ref":30},{"ana":511},{"lettering":642,"dimensions":656},[643,644],"Thinly incised broad letters of regular height, without serifs or marked terminations to the strokes. Alpha has straight bar; Beta has closed loops, in the second instance separated from one another. Sigma has parallel top and bottom strokes, the mid-strokes meeting slightly over halfway across.",{"_":645,"ref":646},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                ",[647,648,649,650,651,652,655],{"_":36,"target":37},{"_":39,"target":40},{"_":42,"target":43},{"_":45,"target":46},{"_":72,"target":73},{"_":653,"target":654},"Σ tyoe3.2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html",{"_":105,"target":106},[657,661],{"type":124,"l":658,"from":126,"to":659,"h":660,"unit":127},"Line 1-3","line3","60",{"type":129,"l":130,"from":126,"to":131,"h":590,"unit":127},{"_":663,"notBefore":519,"notAfter":594,"evidence":664},"Letters of the 3rd century BCE; the apparent double kingship reference suggests the Hieronian period","lettering, titulature",[666,667],{"_":138,"type":139,"ref":140},{"_":142,"type":143,"ref":144},[669],[147,148],{"_":241,"role":242,"ref":243},{"_":159,"mainLang":160,"languages":672},[159],{"n":163,"url":674,"height":675,"width":676,"desc":677,"surfaceType":168},"ISic003009_tiled.tif","2844px","3672px","Photo J. Prag 2018",[],[172,172,680,681,682,417,178],"Gentili, 1961, Nuovi elementi di epigrafia siracusana","Manganaro, 1963, Tauromenitana: un calendario romano di Tauromenion","Manganaro, 1965, Ricerche di antichità e di epigrafia siceliote",[183,183,684,685,686,428,189],"CBDGFVEG","NF8RRH7M","RGTHAFKT",[688,689,690,209,17,217,197,198,199,2